# Production build defaults. SAFE TO COMMIT — every value here is a public
# NEXT_PUBLIC_* that ships to the browser anyway (the Firebase web config is
# not secret; see .env.local for the same note).
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL is intentionally NOT set here — the deploy passes it
# as a build arg (https://<your-domain>) so it tracks the real host. Locally,
# `npm run build` without that arg falls back to http://localhost:8000.

# ─── Firebase web config (project: liquemix) — drives "Enquire → Google" ───
